FIRMWARE DEVELOPMENT
--------------------
STEP 1 - Clone Repo (Rosetta Terminal)
    cd ~/
    mkdir pico
    cd pico
    git clone -b master https://github.com/micropython/micropython.git
    cd micropython
    git pull
    git submodule update --init lib/mbedtls lib/pico-sdk lib/tinyusb
    MAC M1
        sudo port upgrade outdated
        sudo port selfupdate
        sudo port install arm-none-eabi-gcc
    Ubuntu/WSL
        sudo apt update
        sudo apt install cmake gcc-arm-none-eabi libnewlib-arm-none-eabi build-essential
    make -C mpy-cross
STEP 2 - Update main.c [COMMENT LINES]
    cd ports/rp2
    cp main.c
    cd py
    cp obj.c
STEP 3 - Edit main.py [UNCOMMENT LINES]
    while True:
        try:
            try:
                demo.play()
                file_manager.update_games_won()
                menu.system()
            except:  # noqa
                pass
        except:  # noqa
            while True:
                pass
STEP 4 - cd modules [COPY ALL .py FILES INTO THIS DIR]
STEP 5 - vim _boot.py [ADD LINE TO BOTTOM]
    import main
STEP 6 - cd ..
STEP 7 - make submodules
STEP 8 - make clean
STEP 9 - make
    edit CMakeLists.txt
        line 324
            # -Werror
STEP 10 - cp build-PICO/firmware.uf2 /Volumes/RPI-RP2/

Supplemental Instructions: Mass Convert PNG Images to 240x320
-------------------------------------------------------------
https://redketchup.io/bulk-image-resizer

Supplemental Instructions: Convert To .raw & Copy Files To SD Card (EXPERIMENTAL DEV MODE ONLY)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# cd to Tarot-Badge directory
# copy Tarot Card Images into the deck directory (KEEP A BACKUP OF ORIGINALS!)
# NOTE: PLEASE NAME FILES EXACTLY AS THEY ARE IN deck FOLDER FOR NEW DECKS
# NOTE: this will convert the files to 240x320 raw
./convert_to_raw.sh decks/Shitty-Deck/
# NOTE: this will convert all the files in deck and create a dir called deck-raw and copy the .raw files into it
# copy all the files in deck-raw to sd drive
./copy_files_to_sd_card.sh decks/Shitty-Deck/ Shitty-Deck
# NOTE: this will copy files directly to the sd card without having to remove the card it and place in a sd reader

Supplemental Instructions: Convert Single Image File To .raw
------------------------------------------------------------
# manually convert a single image (.png, jpg, etc.) to 240x320 .raw
./convert_single_image_to_raw.sh
# NOTE: this will create a single 240x320 .raw file